<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="273" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="4.[136,1452,1808,2087]" pageId="4" pageNumber="273">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,294,1988,2014]" pageId="4" pageNumber="273">Ecology:</emphasis>
—While no other data on the physical and chemical characteristics of the collecting site were obtained, the associated diatom flora is diverse, with unnamed species of 
<taxonomicName authority="Thwaites" authorityName="Thwaites" box="[857,1102,2024,2050]" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Aulacoseiraceae" genus="Aulacoseira" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Aulacoseirales" pageId="4" pageNumber="273" phylum="Ochrophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[857,992,2024,2050]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="273">Aulacoseira</emphasis>
Thwaites
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Krammer" authorityName="Krammer" box="[1158,1416,2025,2051]" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Cymbellaceae" genus="Encyonopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Cymbellales" pageId="4" pageNumber="273" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1158,1300,2025,2050]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="273">Encyonopsis</emphasis>
Krammer
</taxonomicName>
, as well as 
<taxonomicName authority="Bahls (2013: 15)" authorityName="Bahls" authorityPageNumber="15" authorityYear="2013" box="[222,620,2060,2087]" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Cavinulaceae" genus="Cavinula" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Naviculales" pageId="4" pageNumber="273" phylum="Ochrophyta" rank="species" species="davisiae">
<emphasis box="[222,424,2060,2086]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="273">Cavinula davisiae</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Bahls, L. L." box="[432,620,2060,2087]" pageId="4" pageNumber="273" pagination="7 - 28" refId="ref3339" refString="Bahls, L. L. (2013) New diatoms (Bacillariophyta) from western North America. Phytotaxa 82 (1): 7 - 28. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / phytotaxa. 82.1.2" type="journal article" year="2013">Bahls (2013: 15)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and several species of cymbelloid diatoms being present.
</paragraph>
